data.value: Specifies a column that contains a Multidimensional Expressions (MDX) expression used to aggregate measures for the attribute. This property overrides the AggregateFunction property of the given measure.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_DerivedFromColumnId
data.value: Used only for attributes of CalcuatedTables. This property stores the information as to source column from which the current attribute was calculated from. This is managed by the engine currently. Client/User don't set this property.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_DerivedFromTableId
data.value: Used only for attributes of CalcuatedTables. This property stores the information as to source table from which the current attribute was calculated from. This is managed by the engine currently. Client/User don't set this property.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_DiscretizationBucketCount
data.value: Specifies the number of buckets in which to discretize (group) members of the attribute. The method used to discretize the members is set by the DiscretizationMethod property.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_DiscretizationMethod
data.value: Specifies the method used to discretize (group) the members of the attribute. The number of buckets created by discretizing the members is set by the DiscretizationBucketCount.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_EstimatedCount
data.value: Specifies the number of members in the attribute. This number is either the amount last counted by Analysis Services, or a user-provided estimate of the member count.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_ExtendedType

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_FormatString
data.value: Specifies the format used by clients when displaying the member caption.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_GroupingBehavior
data.value: Indicates whether client applications should discourage users from grouping on this attribute.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_HasLineage
data.value: Used only for attributes of CalcuatedTables. This property stores the information as to whether the current column has direct lineage with the source column identified by DerivedFromTableId and DerivedFromColumnId. This is managed by the engine currently. Client/User don't set this property.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_InstanceSelection
data.value: Specifies the recommended means by which a client UI should allow selection of a member.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_IsAggregatable
data.value: Indicates whether the attribute can be aggregated in a hierarchy. The attribute hierarchy has an (All) level if is this is True.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_KeyColumns
data.value: Specifies the details of the binding to the column(s) containing the member key(s).

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_MemberNamesUnique
data.value: Indicates whether member names are unique for this attribute (affecting how member unique names are assigned).

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_MembersWithData
data.value: Specifies the treatment of fact data associated with non-leaf members.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_MembersWithDataCaption
data.value: Specifies a template string used to create captions for the system-generated data members.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_NameColumn
data.value: Specifies the details of the binding to the column containing the member name.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_NamingTemplate
data.value: Specifies the definition of how levels in a parent-child hierarchy are named (for example "CEO ; VP "). If not specified, then the system will assign names.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_OrderBy

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_ProcessingState
data.value: Specifies the processing state of the attribute.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_RootMemberIf

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_SkippedLevelsColumn

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_TokenizationBehavior

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_Type

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_UnaryOperatorColumn

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_Usage
data.value: Specifies the usage of the attribute.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_UserEditFlag
data.value: Used only for attributes of CalcuatedTables. This property stores the information as to whether user wants lineage to update the property field or not. This is managed by the engine currently. Client/User don't set this property.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_ValueColumn
data.value: Specifies the details of the binding to the column containing the member value.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DimensionAttribute_VertipaqCompressionHint
data.value: Specifies a hint for the level of the Vertipaq compression algorithm.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Dimension_Language

data.name: PropertyDescription_Dimension_MdxMissingMemberMode

data.name: PropertyDescription_Dimension_ProactiveCaching

data.value: Specifies the type of storage for the dimension.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Dimension_StringStoresCompatibilityLevel
data.value: Indicates the level of compatibility for the string stores of the dimension which is used now or going to be used from the moment of the next full processing of the dimension.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Dimension_Type
data.value: Specifies the type of information contained by the dimension.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Dimension_UnknownMember
data.value: Specifies the existence of an unknown member, and whether that member is visible or hidden. Fact data not associated with a member can be associated with the unknown member.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Dimension_UnknownMemberName
data.value: Specifies the caption for the unknown member in the default language. If not specified, the default value "Unknown" is used.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Dimension_WriteEnabled
data.value: Specifies the dimension can be updated by client applications.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DrillThroughAction_Default
data.value: Specifies the drillthrough action default.

data.name: PropertyDescription_DrillThroughAction_MaximumRows
data.value: Specifies the maximum number of rows that will be returned on drillthrough.

data.name: PropertyDescription_ErrorConfiguration_CalculationError

data.name: PropertyDescription_ErrorConfiguration_KeyDuplicate

data.name: PropertyDescription_ErrorConfiguration_KeyErrorLimit
data.value: Specifies the maximum number of key errors that can occur before either processing stops, or processing continues but key errors are no longer logged. The KeyErrorLimitAction property specifies which action is taken.

data.name: PropertyDescription_ErrorConfiguration_KeyErrorLimitAction
data.value: Specifies the action taken by the server upon encountering the maximum number of key errors specified in the KeyErrorLimit property. The server either stops processing, or continues processing but no longer logs key errors.

data.name: PropertyDescription_ErrorConfiguration_KeyErrorLogFile
data.value: Specifies the file to which all key errors will be logged.

data.name: PropertyDescription_ErrorConfiguration_KeyNotFound
data.value: Specifies the action taken by the server upon encountering a key that cannot be found.

data.name: PropertyDescription_ErrorConfiguration_NullKeyConvertedToUnknown
data.value: Specifies the action taken by the server upon converting a null key to the key for the unknown member.

data.name: PropertyDescription_ErrorConfiguration_NullKeyNotAllowed
data.value: Specifies the action taken by the server upon encountering a null key in the case where a null key is not valid.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Hierarchy_AllMemberName

data.name: PropertyDescription_Kpi_DisplayFolder

data.name: PropertyDescription_Kpi_ParentKpiID

data.value: Specifies a Multidimensional Expressions (MDX) expression that returns the status of the key performance indicator (KPI). This is a normalized expression returning values between -1 (bad) and 1 (good).

data.value: Specifies the recommended graphical representation for the status.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Kpi_Trend
data.value: Specifies a Multidimensional Expressions (MDX) expression that returns the trend of the key performance indicator (KPI) over time. This is a normalized expression returning values between -1 (getting much worse over time) and 1 (getting much better over time).

data.name: PropertyDescription_Kpi_TrendGraphic
data.value: Specifies the recommended graphical representation for the trend.

data.name: PropertyDescription_Kpi_Value
data.value: Specifies a Multidimensional Expressions (MDX) expression that returns the actual value of the key performance indicator (KPI).

data.name: PropertyDescription_Kpi_Weight
data.value: Specifies a Multidimensional Expressions (MDX) expression that returns the weight of the key performance indicator (KPI). This is most applicable when the KPI has a parent KPI, where it provides information to the client as to the weight of the contribution to its parent.

Either the linking object is refreshed (NotPersisted) or becomes invalid (Metadata) upon changes to the underlying object. The value of 'All' applies to local cubes.

data.name: PropertyDescription_MeasureGroup_ProcessingMode
data.value: Indicates whether processed data is available after all aggregations have been computed (Regular) or immediately after data has been loaded (LazyAggregations). This setting will be used as the default for new partitions created for the measure group.

data.name: PropertyDescription_MeasureGroup_ProcessingPriority
data.value: Specifies the priority for processing the measure group.

data.name: PropertyDescription_MeasureGroup_Source
data.value: Specifies the source of the measure group.

data.name: PropertyDescription_MeasureGroup_StorageLocation

data.name: PropertyDescription_MeasureGroup_StorageMode
